This paper investigates the effectiveness of adblocking filters on websites, which falls under the category of web security and privacy (cs.CR). The study also involves data collection and analysis of web content, which could be categorized under web science (cs.WEB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of specialized filters to target anti-adblocking logic, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) since ads often contain multimedia content. Finally, the study could also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI) since it involves analyzing the behavior of websites and advertisers in response to adblocking filters.
